Package org.postgresql.pljava.pg

Class TriggerImpl

java.lang.Object
org.postgresql.pljava.pg.CatalogObjectImpl
org.postgresql.pljava.pg.TriggerImpl
All Implemented Interfaces:
CatalogObject, CatalogObject.Addressed<Trigger>, CatalogObject.Named<Lexicals.Identifier.Simple>, Trigger, CatalogObjectImpl.Nonshared<Trigger>
class TriggerImpl extends CatalogObjectImpl implements CatalogObjectImpl.Nonshared<Trigger>, Trigger
Implements Trigger.

This implementation, at least at first, will have an unusual limitation: its accessor methods (other than those of Addressed) may only work when called by a trigger function or its language handler within the scope of the function's preparation and execution. Some may be unimplemented even then, as noted in the documentation of the methods themselves.

That spares it from having to deal with getting the content from pg_trigger, or cache lifetime, or invalidation; it can operate from the copy PostgreSQL supplies for the trigger function call, during the scope of the call.

At least for now, then, it simply extends CatalogObjectImpl directly rather than CatalogObjectImpl.Addressed, needing none of the caching machinery in the latter.
